<br>
My guild uses a fixed DKP system. We charge ridiculess prices and give crap for dkp. (time clear is 20ish dkp, all phase 3+ loot is 45+dkp...bps / quarm loot are 65 dkp+) Thus, all of our hardcore raiders dont buy anything unless its a MAJOR upgrade...so stuff rots. A LOT. <br>
<br>
Like yesterday...our first two deathcallers stonewinds dropped. Officers decided 35dkp for 1. Hmm. Ya. Our 2 bards at the raid both said if that was going to happen, those instruments would rot. And when they did rot...people got PISSED at us. &quot;WHY DONT YOU WANT THAT?!?!&quot; &quot;Hmm would you pay 2 time raids worth of DKP for an item you'd use only during duels? (manadrain)&quot; &quot;No...&quot; &quot;Neither would we. So STFU plz.&quot; (we had to pay the same dkp for our rathe drums / water lutes. BEFORE time, when we were making 10ish dkp a week...its RIDICULESS.)<br>
<br>
Im not an advocate for our system. Its crap. Like I've seen 2 Amulets of Crystal Dreams rot...and that would be a MAJOR upgrade to NUMEROUS people (myself included.) I've let em rot till I have my Rizlona's bp / Quarm hammer (1st in line for both.) Then I might buy one...maybe. All of the other hardcore raiders think like me...we dont buy unless its a MAJOR MAJOR MAJOR freaking upgrade, even then...it sucks cause it hurts your dkp so badly. So our major raiders havent looted real upgrades in months...we've all be hoarding for certain items. Like I said...lots rots. And rotting BLOWS. BLOWS. <br>
<br>
I think a bidding system would help solve stuff...that or just freaking reduce prices by 20ish dkp. But NOOOOOO Our officers HAVE to have DKP inflation control! *whine whine whine* Ya. It seems to be working REAL DAMN FREAKING WELL. Our highest 20 DKP holders all have around 600ish. Our lowest has negative 40. Out of 140ish. You need only like 90 dkp to win most loot. Unless its a BP...then you need 600+. Ya its stupid system. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://img65.photobucket.com/albums/v199/klondorwarrior/orginal_copy.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
