<br>
Events earn points according to the difficultly of the event divided by the number of people there. So a full raid gives out fewer points per person. As time goes on, an event will be downgraded so fewer points are handed out. Early arrival is rewarded by points for clearing and logs will be taken at various times. So someone there from start to finish will earn more points, but those who can only be there for part of the raid will get something.<br>
<br>
We also have rot prices which are 1/8th full. If no one puts in for something it's offered to recruits and then alts at full, then put up for rot. However, anyone willing to pay full gets priority over the rot price. That means you can log in an alt who wasn't even at the event if he can pay full. This inhibits playing the rot game, because you can lose out. Normal bidding is based on your current points. Rot is decided randomly. May be a roll, may be the person closest to zero, may be first tell. Since you don't know how the rot reward will be determined, you can't predict if you'll get it or not. Seems to work for the most part. <br>
<br>
It doesn't help the guild to have things actually rot. You all put in your time and you want to make the guild stronger as a whole. Your system is seriously flawed if solid upgrades go to waste like that. Sounds like time to start a revolution on your message boards. Bitching here isn't going to help. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=suladasbardspeed>Suladas Bardspeed</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 306<br> <font color=#330000>(6/4/04 2:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19464.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sigh, ELP vs DKP?</span><hr size=1> I've tried...time and time again (hahah stupid time...) and noone listens to sula <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . We did just start a new rot rule at a combined effort of bitching between me and apps tho. If an item is rotting then we call it 1/2 off and /random to see who the winner is.<br>
