<br>
ELP ( Event Lotto Points ) is a system started in October of 2000 by the guild Inner Circle.  At its' heart it's a system where members earn points for successfully defeating a boss mob and then can bid, auction style, these points to earn loot.  Bonus ELP was awarded for first kills or particularly onerous encounters.  As well the ELP earned per mob dropped as the encounter became more routine.<br>
<br>
Items generally start off with no fixed cost if it has never dropped for the guild before, with subsequent starting prices being determined as half the price of the last winning bid for that item.<br>
<br>
What was nice about the system is that it didn't inherently reward seniority as some systems do.  New members could save up their points and compete on an even playing field for items with long time members.  As well the &quot;market&quot; determined what an item would cost.  However, while this was usually good, it did tend to allow price fixing by classes for class specific items.<br>
<br>
Overall it was a good system if you take into consideration the tweaks implemented over the past 3.5 years.  Unfortunately, the Inner Circle  website has been converted to a WoW Beta website, or you could read the actual rules we used.<br>
